{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BS4gtYMSfZ26t2S2dPUtwJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build is green. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Harness: `h5_group_link_fuzzer`**\n\nThe harness targets the group open and link traversal attack surface by exercising the full API call chain a real HDF5 application would use:\n\n1. **`H5Fopen`** (RDONLY) — writes fuzz bytes to a temp file and opens it as an HDF5 file\n2. **`H5Gopen2(\"/\", ...)`** — opens the root group, triggering B-tree/fractal-heap parsing\n3. **`H5Gget_info`** — reads group metadata (storage type: compact vs. dense, nlink count)\n4. **`H5Giterate`** — iterates via the legacy symbol-table / B-tree code path; callback calls `H5Lget_info2` per link to probe compact→dense transitions\n5. **`H5Lvisit2`** — recursive link visitation via the modern v2 B-tree / fractal-heap path, run with both `H5_INDEX_NAME` and `H5_INDEX_CRT_ORDER` to cover both ordering code paths\n6. **`H5Lget_info_by_idx2`** — queries link info by position index when links exist\n7. A second `H5Gopen2(\"group\", ...)` pass exercises named non-root groups\n8. `H5Gclose` / `H5Fclose` on every opened identifier\n\nThe harness uses `H5F_ACC_RDONLY` (no writes to the file) and suppresses HDF5 error output with `H5Eset_auto2(NULL, NULL)` to keep fuzzer output clean. Callbacks always return 0 to continue iteration, never recurse beyond what the API itself controls, and touch no harness-owned buffers unsafely."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":268,"cache_read_input_tokens":54957,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":268,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"23ddc9e0-d3f9-4675-87cb-79190a925bcc","uuid":"7ee51903-472a-4f14-a2aa-70446ea6721e"}
